#!/usr/bin/env python3
# =============================================================================
# DVBS2_TR - one executable + one config (link.toml) for a low-latency DVB-S2
# video/data link over a USRP B210 software-defined radio.
#
# "One config, one binary" operator surface. All backend/library diagnostics are
# silenced so nothing but DVBS2_TR's own output reaches the terminal; low-level
# radio device messages are routed to a log file under the run directory.
#
#   DVBS2_TR --config link.toml check     preflight: runtime, radio, config, rates
#   DVBS2_TR --config link.toml tx        transmit  (video per [payload], or raw with --raw)
#   DVBS2_TR --config link.toml rx        receive   (video per [payload], or raw with --raw)
#   DVBS2_TR --config link.toml bench     raw-data link self-test (TX feeds, RX reads, latency)
#   DVBS2_TR --config link.toml duplex    transmit + receive at once on one radio
#   DVBS2_TR --config link.toml rates     print the auto-scaled MODCOD net-rate/resolution
#
# Resolution auto-scales to the MODCOD net rate when [payload].resolution = "auto".
# =============================================================================
